{
  "stem": "25912.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But she wasn't bright enough.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Again, to her it really didn't mean anything our being Jewish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It made no difference.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She's had worked for other Jewish families.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She was devoted to us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She was the one came to nurse me when I had scarlet fever.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She was always there for me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So what can one say?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She lived quite near what the part would became the little ghetto in [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the shopping-- there was a big marketplace very near.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that's where we went.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she had offered to have my grandmother to stay.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my mother spoke to my grandmother on the telephone and she was trying to make arrangements for her to leave the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it was slightly more complicated because my grandmother having been educated in Germany although she didn't speak Yiddish she spoke German.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She did have an accent in Polish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she also had more Semitic features perhaps than my mother and myself.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that's was an added hazard.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But my nurse was quite prepared to have her to stay.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But by that time I think mother was getting wary.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Maniunia, but I can't remember what her-- I can't remember what her surname was.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Maniunia, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I've got her photograph somewhere but I can't remember what her name was, surname.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had, we moved on from there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All this time we were being looked after by this friend who had helped us with food in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nothing.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just what we--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You couldn't take anything with you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But during that time and afterwards one got used to having nothing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I found it quite difficult after the war to start getting attached to things because things were something which you left behind.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They didn't matter.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
